                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18400406-1301-offence-1 t18400406-name-1572"></join>John Roberts</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1573" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1573" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1573" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1573" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>CHARLOTTE ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Roberts—we keep a china-shop in the Broadway, Deptford. On the 8th of April we lost these plates from the step of the door—I did not see who took them, but the po<lb></lb>liceman brought them back, and I then missed them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Can you swear to these plates? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—we know our maker's make—I thought there was about a dozen, but there are thirteen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1574" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1574" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1574" type="surname" value="REDDEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1574" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL REDDEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a lodging-house at Deptford—the prisoner brought these plates to me, and I told him to take them away, because he said he had <hi rend="italic">pulled</hi> them—he did not ask me to buy them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1575" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1575" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1575" type="surname" value="PROVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1575" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PROVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I took the prisoner in Mill-lane, Deptford—I saw these plates on his table—he said they were his—that he had purchased three dozen in London, and these were the remainder.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184004060274"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> There are thousands of this kind in London—I bought them, intending to sell them on the road.</p>
